review_text: I normally use the Olly Extra Strength 5mg melatonin gummies, but the store I went to was out so I thought I'd try the Natrol brand 5mg gummies. This gummy states to only take 1 instead of the 2 that Olly wants you to take. The taste is very good. Night 1 I took 1 gummy as directed and I was tired for literally 2 days straight! The next day I woke up at like 3pm! I vowed to never take them again when last night I had a bad migraine and my headache medicine has caffeine in it, and I really wanted sleep so I figured I'd take 1/2 a gummy (and a small portion of half at that!) Well here it is the next night 830, and I've wasted another day because I am so tired and feel drained. Obviously these gummies are NOT for me, and the gentleness of Olly works better for me. review_text: I've been using these melatonin gummies for the past year now and they taste just as good today as they did when I first had them. I usually get taste fatigue on products I've been using for months, but I'm happy to say that the taste of these gummies is great for me personally. Sweet, but not overwhelmingly sweet, and with no lingering aftertaste. Moving on to the effects of the gummies: they work! I can naturally stay up all night if left to my own devices, so I pop two of these gummies on sleepless nights where I am on my computer or on my phone. After about 20-40 minutes (depends on if I had a late dinner, did exercise, or am fatigued from the day), I start feeling the subtle effects of the gummies taking place and log off my computer to actually prepare for bed. The ONLY complaint I may have is that I wake up very groggy after taking melatonin, but I attribute this grogginess to my bad late-night sleep habits and forced early wake-ups due to my job. When I take these during the weekend and have uninterrupted, unlimited sleep, I feel very rested and have great sleep. I won't take away a star on the sleep quality because of the grogginess though, as that is my own fault and would have been the case for any melatonin product. Highly recommend trying these-- I can't imagine using any other melatonin product now!

review_text: I had been using Ibuprofen PM, which is basically Ibuprofen and Benadryl. I have trouble falling asleep and staying asleep. I had gotten some Liquid IV sleep formula because I love Liquid IV and wanted to see if melatonin would help. The Liquid IV sleep helped greatly, except it is rather pricey and I don't like the taste of their sleep formula, so I tried these based off the reviews. Being a small female, I opted for 1 before bedtime and it really does work in about 30 minutes. The taste is amazing. Last night I was in a deaf sleep until my cat started meowing loudly at 5 am. I was infuriated because if I wake up for any reason before my alarm, no matter how tired I am, I cannot fall back asleep easily so I either lose a good hour or more of sleep or stay up and feel tired and groggy all day. Well it dawned on me to take another one of these. Let me tell you it worked like a charm. I was able to fall back to sleep much sooner PLUS I woke up feeling clear headed and refreshed. I would never take an Ibuprofen PM again when waking in the middle of the night, no way, but going to sleep on the first 1 (5 MG) then taking the second one when rudely awakened, absolutely did the trick. I picked up overtime at work today and felt pretty darn good. Highly recommend these. I actually feel human again after many years. Thank you!

review_text: My shrink recommended I try this when I kept needing a higher and higher dose of sleeping meds to fall asleep. I take ONE chew (5mg) and 2 of my sleeping meds. Now I fall asleep gently, I stay asleep (courtesy of my prescription meds), and I wake up with no weird grogginess or flatness. I am VERY skeptical of herbal supplements because they are completely unregulated. Companies could put chewed bat wings in their supplements, tell you it's Vitamin D, and you'd never know. So I took the risk for you and I promise, these work. Now, these will not override you having the TV running and playing Gardenscapes on your phone. This ain't Ambien, y'all. You can read on your Kindle if you want. It's so nice to just drift off to sleep. Also, pay attention to the dosage instructions. 5mg at first, then go to 10mg if it doesn't help. Do. Not. Exceed. 10mg. It is Not Good. You will not feel good. Also note that for best results, you should take melatonin about 30 minutes before bedtime. By that time, your room should also be at least dim if not dark, and you should be showering, brushing your teeth, whatever. No computer. No phone. This really can work, if you do it right. Don't do it right and you might as well eat your money because it'll do as much good.

product_title: Natrol Melatonin Sleep Aid Gummy, Fall Asleep Faster, Stay Asleep Longer, 2 Gummies Per Serving, Drug Free and Gelatin Free, 10mg, 90 Strawberry Flavored Gummies
review_text: These things are potent and taste great! I use sleep gummies to help me go to sleep early, and so I've tried a few brands. Specifically, I compared these to the Nature Made Melatonin Adult Strawberry Gummy and the Nature's Bounty Tropical Punch Sleep Gummy. The Natrol Melatonin gummies are strong, packing 5mg into each gummy. Compare this to 2.5g in the Nature Made and 3mg (and 200mg L-Theanine) in the Nature's Bounty gummies. The non-gelatin Natrol gummies taste very true to strawberry, and they dissolve and chew with a different mouthfeel than the other two gummies. They definitely break up and dissolve more quickly and don't get stuck in your teeth the same as the other gummies. If you're very sensitive to melatonin, these may hit you hard and possibly leave you a bit drowsy. The other two have less per gummy but can be taken in small multiples to dial in a good dose. I highly recommend these new gummies, specifically for taste, potency, and chew-ability.

review_text: Another melatonin product that did not work as promised. This claims to both help you "Fall Asleep Faster" and "Stay Asleep Longer" but both claims were false for me. I tried these 2 nights in a row, taking the full 10 mg dose each time. Both times they took over an hour to work, and the max sleep I got was 5 uninterrupted hours on the second night. This is not enough for me; ideally I would get at least 10 hours but even 8 hours would have been acceptable for this product. It also left me groggy. I've been getting up too early, so last night I even stayed up later before taking them in hopes of getting a good, long sleep. After waking up the short 5 hours later I tried to taking just one gummy to help me get back to sleep, then about an hour and a half later another one. And I'm still awake (mildly groggy) writing this review. I will 'play around' with this product to see if I can get it to work for me. but as of right now I'm on the fence about repurchasing, and don't recommend if other melatonin products haven't worked well for you. (Also tried their Sleep+Calm variety and that was HORRIBLE! )

product_title: Natrol Melatonin Sleep Aid Gummy, Fall Asleep Faster, Stay Asleep Longer, 2 Gummies Per Serving, Drug Free and Gelatin Free, 10mg, 90 Strawberry Flavored Gummies
review_text: I have mixed feelings about Melatonin, and about supplements in general. Because they aren't strictly regulated by the FDA, there is never a guarantee that what's purported to be in the product is actually in it. John Oliver had an interesting segment on this subject (and "Dr. Oz") that's worth checking out. However.... my wife and son both take melatonin at night to help them sleep, and it has usually fallen to me to order or buy these supplements for them. Ironic, right? Nonetheless, in this regard, I do appreciate the "bang for your buck" of these Natrol gummies, with 5mg per gummy at a good price point. 2 or 3 mgs is what they usually take, so they've been cutting these in half. The berry flavor reportedly tastes "pretty good." Do they work? It's hard to say. Some nights my son reports waking up multiple times, other nights he sleeps like a rock. Consumer Reports quotes a study that found "people taking the drugs fall asleep only 7 minutes faster and sleep 8 minutes longer on average". It also suggest you look for a "USP Verified" logo on supplements, which tends to indicate more thorough vetting.... I don't see such a logo on this bottle. On top of that, it's generally recommended to take it episodially, or, as Dr. Chris Winter (author of "The Sleep Solution") says, "You should give yourself a time limit, such as for four or five days," he says, adding that they should be taken for a very specific reason, such as during an unusual bout of insomnia or when you're traveling across time zones. "When that thing has run its course, you should stop." But many people take it every day, which, it is said, could sabotage the effectiveness of your body's internal clock. But I don't want to be one to judge.... to each their own. If I am not getting any negative reports from my better halves, I will likely continue to order this product for them. 3.5 stars to balance it all out!
review_header: Good value for a powerful 5mg = 1 gummy dose

review_text: These things not only didn't work for me they turned my intestines inside out. I purchased these back in August and the first few times I took them at night they did help me get to sleep. I followed the recommended dosage of two (2) 10mg gummies, the first night I was able to sleep for about 6 hours and that is good for me as I usually only get 4 to 5 hours of sleep. However on the second, third and fourth nights I would wake up at around 2:OO am and would be so dizzy I couldn't walk. So I reduced the dosage to one gummy a night and I was back to sleeping maybe 5 hours but at least I wouldn't wake up with the room spinning. I continued the one per night regiment and after a month I started having constant intestine grumbling sounds and very loose stools. I could not for the life of me figure out why my stomach and intestines were dealing me such fits. Finally out of desperation I quit taking these melatonin gummies and after a couple of weeks my gut problems subsided and I'm now able to have more normal bowel movements. And my gut doesn't sound like it has a lion in it roaring all the time. I would not recommend these so called sleep aids to anyone, as far as I'm concerned the gummies are made of snake oil.

product_title: Natrol Melatonin Sleep Aid Gummy, Fall Asleep Faster, Stay Asleep Longer, 2 Gummies Per Serving, Drug Free and Gelatin Free, 10mg, 90 Strawberry Flavored Gummies
review_text: A substantial dose of melatonin in these candy-like drops. They're reasonably priced, with a higher 5mg dose than the 2mg I usually see. The big question, do they work? That's hard to tell with a product like this, because of the placebo effect, and also because somebody who's paying enough attention to bedtime to plan to take one of these 30 minutes before bed is already focused on sleeping better. But empirically, they definitely work. I'm a night-owl, so I often feel very alert an hour or two past when I "should" be trying to sleep. Taking one of these instead produces a pleasant sleepiness at that time, like the way you feel when you get up during the night-- you're awake, but could go right back to sleep. Falling asleep is faster, staying asleep is more solid. It seems to work as described. I've also read that studies indicate melatonin is one of the few measurably effective ways to cope with jet-lag. Travelers take note... I did notice that if I underslept (had to get up early) after taking this melatonin, I was groggier than I would have been otherwise. It's also worth noting these drops have 10 calories of sugar per dose, with an overly sweet taste. I'd much rather have had a formulation that tasted less like it was aimed at small children, but that's a foible of many products aimed at American consumers, so I don't drop my rating. For the almost non-existent side-effects associated with using melatonin, this is going to be superior to medicating for most users, and certainly better than old-wives remedies like warm milk. And it's cheap! If you're trying to sleep more consistently, or sleep more solidly, or go to bed a little earlier, give this stuff a try. Recommended.
review_header: seems to work well, but could do w/o the sugar
